<?php $__env->startSection('content'); ?><p>Three Atalanta players have tested positive for COVID-19 but all are asymptomatic and have been isolated, the Serie A club said in a statement on Monday.</p>

<p>The tests were carried out ahead of Atalanta's Monday return to training ahead of the new season, due to start on September 19.</p>

<p>The players were not named, and Atalanta said training went ahead as normal for the rest of the squad.</p>

<p>Three Atalanta players have tested positive for coronavirus but they are all asymptomatic</p>

<p>Atalanta finished third in Serie A last season and reached the quarter-finals of the Champions League, where they lost 2-1 to Paris St Germain in Lisbon.</p>

<p>The club is based in the city of Bergamo which was at the epicentre of the coronavirus outbreak in Italy earlier this year.</p>

<p>Gian Piero Gasperini's squad continued to train as normal ahead of Serie A's return next month</p>

<p>Italy have clarified their position for the start of the Serie A season to fall in line with the beginning of the German Bundesliga. </p>

<p>Fixtures for the new campaign are set to be released on September 2.</p>

<p>The 2019-20 Serie A season reached its conclusion on August 1 before Atalanta, Juventus, Inter and Napoli continued with involvement in European competitions</p>
